HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 280
BY REPRESENTATIVE MELERINE
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates May 18, 2026, as Necrotizing Enterocolitis
Awareness Day in Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Monday, May 18, 2026, as Necrotizing Enterocolitis Awareness Day in
3 Louisiana.
4 WHEREAS, necrotizing enterocolitis (NEC) is an intestinal disease that primarily
5 affects premature and medically fragile infants; the disease causes a severe inflammatory
6 process that can lead to intestinal tissue damage and is the most common cause of death in
7 hospitalized premature infants after two weeks of age; and
8 WHEREAS, babies born prematurely or with a medical complication, like congenital
9 heart disease, are most at risk of NEC; thousands of babies develop NEC each year, and
10 hundreds of babies die from this complex intestinal condition; many babies only live for a
11 few hours or days after NEC is diagnosed; and
12 WHEREAS, surgery for NEC is not curative, and babies who survive often have
13 lifelong neurological and nutritional complications; and
14 WHEREAS, NEC results in significant hospitalization expenses per year and roughly
15 nineteen percent of neonatal healthcare expenditures in the United States, with an estimated
16 cost of two hundred thousand dollars or more for each case of surgical necrotizing
17 enterocolitis; and
18 WHEREAS, although the risk of necrotizing enterocolitis cannot be fully eliminated,
19 preventative measures are effective at reducing risks; feeding breast milk is one of the most
20 effective ways to help prevent necrotizing enterocolitis in medically fragile infants; and
