1 WHEREAS, more data is needed to better understand how and why NEC occurs in
2 infants; and
3 WHEREAS, because of disparities and variation in care, black infants are
4 disproportionately affected by NEC compared to white infants; and
5 WHEREAS, to build a world without necrotizing enterocolitis and improve outcomes
6 for infants and families, awareness must be raised about this devastating neonatal disease.
7 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
8 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Monday, May 18, 2026, as Necrotizing
9 Enterocolitis Awareness Day in Louisiana and does hereby encourage citizens to support
10 initiatives that raise awareness about this disease.
